abstract: The purpose of this column has been to show how we can learn from those who have had financial success (or bigger flops) to improve our own financial lives.
snippet: The purpose of this column has been to show how we can learn from those who have had financial success (or bigger flops) to improve our own financial lives.
lead_paragraph: When my first Wealth Matters column ran in December 2008, I wrote that I wanted to examine the strategies the wealthy used to manage their money and their lives in a way that people with far less money could learn from.

snippet: Mr. Cline was a well-known philanthropist and Republican donor who began working in the coal industry in West Virginia.
lead_paragraph: Chris Cline, a billionaire entrepreneur, philanthropist and political donor once called the “King of Coal,” died Thursday in a helicopter crash in the Bahamas that officials said killed seven people.

abstract: Nearly every Democrat running for president supports the idea, a sharp change from even a few years ago. Here’s a look at the policy behind the politics.
snippet: Nearly every Democrat running for president supports the idea, a sharp change from even a few years ago. Here’s a look at the policy behind the politics.
lead_paragraph: Providing comprehensive health coverage to undocumented immigrants has long been nothing more than a wouldn’t-it-be-nice item on the far left’s wish list. But in the crowded field of candidates vying for the 2020 Democratic presidential nomination, nearly everyone supports it.

abstract: If an agreement is reached, it will underline how much Broadcom, a semiconductor giant, has had to change its acquisition strategy after a humbling takeover defeat last year.
snippet: If an agreement is reached, it will underline how much Broadcom, a semiconductor giant, has had to change its acquisition strategy after a humbling takeover defeat last year.
lead_paragraph: Broadcom has set its sights on acquiring a well-known name in cybersecurity software, in a further strategy shift after the Trump administration blocked it last year from purchasing another chip maker on national security grounds.

abstract: ‘Medicare for all’ would essentially do away with private insurance, a fact that some politicians seem reluctant to emphasize.
snippet: ‘Medicare for all’ would essentially do away with private insurance, a fact that some politicians seem reluctant to emphasize.
lead_paragraph: The Medicare for All Act written by Senator Bernie Sanders would cover not just standard medical services, but also vision, dental and long-term care. It would offer more health benefits than the world’s leading universal health care systems.

headline_main: DealBook Briefing: Say Hello to the E.C.B.’s New Chief, Christine Lagarde

abstract: The president, in a pair of tweets, said he would nominate Judy Shelton, a Fed critic, and Christopher Waller, a St. Louis Fed official, to sit on the Fed board.
snippet: The president, in a pair of tweets, said he would nominate Judy Shelton, a Fed critic, and Christopher Waller, a St. Louis Fed official, to sit on the Fed board.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump, who has spent months assailing the Federal Reserve for its interest rate policies, said he planned to nominate Christopher Waller, a longtime regional Fed official, and Judy Shelton, a Fed critic, to serve on the central bank’s seven-member board.

abstract: Tennis has long been known for its prodigies — and the cautionary tales that many of them tell.
snippet: Tennis has long been known for its prodigies — and the cautionary tales that many of them tell.
lead_paragraph: WIMBLEDON, England — Tennis has its latest prodigy in Cori Gauff, the 15-year-old American who upset Venus Williams, once a wonder child herself, in the first round of Wimbledon of Monday.

abstract: A pan-Asian food court in Elmhurst, Queens; a wine bar in Bedford-Stuyvesant, Brooklyn; and more restaurant news.
snippet: A pan-Asian food court in Elmhurst, Queens; a wine bar in Bedford-Stuyvesant, Brooklyn; and more restaurant news.
lead_paragraph: In Northern China, particularly in Beijing, hutongs are old, narrow alleyways. They’re lined with small houses that have courtyards, some of which house restaurants. The branch of Hutong about to open in the Bloomberg L.P. headquarters is in a courtyard, to be sure, but it has turned the far-from-humble space that housed Le Cirque into a statement of jaw-dropping Art Deco grandeur, with a soaring blue and silver dining room and white marble details. “I consider New York to be the Art Deco capital, and I wanted to pay homage to it and also to Art Deco of Shanghai,” said David Yeo, the founder of the Hong Kong-based Aqua Restaurant Group, which owns this Hutong, as well as others in London and Asia. He said his mandate for Robert Angell, the designer, was “no red lanterns, no stereotypes.” This branch contrasts with the one in London, on 33rd floor of the Shard building, which has an Imperial Palace profusion of gilt, black and red. Mr. Yeo’s Hutong restaurants specialize in Northern Chinese food, so expect impressive platters heaped with crisp soft-shell crabs, chile-fueled beef tenderloin ma la style, the inevitable Peking duck and, specifically for New York, deep-fried prawns with pickled vegetables, broad beans with Sichuan sauce, and squid “flowers” with chile dressing. In the evening, dim sum are served in the warmly lit contemporary bar and the dining room. It will also be served for lunch, which starts in a week. (Opens Monday)
